# Research Report: common.sh Role Hierarchy & Planner Sub-Role Integration

## Task: Research common.sh role hierarchy and on-pre-tool-use.sh blocking patterns for planner sub-role
## Task ID: 45, Subtask: 98
## Date: 2026-04-10

---

## Summary

The role detection system uses a two-tier model: **base roles** (`DOEY_ROLE`) determined by pane position, and **team roles** (`DOEY_TEAM_ROLE`) from team definition files. The `interviewer` team role is the existing precedent for granting sub-role exceptions to Subtaskmaster restrictions. No planner-related roles exist yet. The cleanest integration path is to add a `planner` team role following the exact `interviewer` pattern.

---

## 1. How Role Detection Works

### Base Role Detection (on-session-start.sh:45-75)

Roles are determined by **window index + pane index**:

```bash
# on-session-start.sh:45
ROLE="$DOEY_ROLE_ID_WORKER"  # default

# Window 0 = Dashboard
if [ "$WINDOW_INDEX" = "0" ]; then
  case "$PANE_INDEX" in
    0) ROLE="info_panel" ;;
    1) ROLE="$DOEY_ROLE_ID_BOSS" ;;
  esac
# Core Team window (from TASKMASTER_PANE)
elif [ "$WINDOW_INDEX" = "$_core_team_window" ]; then
  case "$PANE_INDEX" in
    0) ROLE="$DOEY_ROLE_ID_COORDINATOR" ;;
    1) ROLE="$DOEY_ROLE_ID_TASK_REVIEWER" ;;
    2) ROLE="$DOEY_ROLE_ID_DEPLOYMENT" ;;
    3) ROLE="$DOEY_ROLE_ID_DOEY_EXPERT" ;;
  esac
else
  # Worker teams: pane 0 = team_lead, others = worker
  mgr_pane=$(_read_team_key "$_team_file" MANAGER_PANE)
  [ "$PANE_INDEX" = "${mgr_pane:-0}" ] && ROLE="$DOEY_ROLE_ID_TEAM_LEAD"
fi
```

The role is written to both `$CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` (env var `DOEY_ROLE`) and `${RUNTIME_DIR}/status/${PANE_SAFE}.role`.

### Team Role Detection (on-session-start.sh:195-206)

A secondary `DOEY_TEAM_ROLE` is read from team definition files:

```bash
# on-session-start.sh:199
_team_role=$(grep "^PANE_${PANE_INDEX}_ROLE=" "$_teamdef_env" | cut -d= -f2-)
# Written to env and status file:
echo "DOEY_TEAM_ROLE=$_team_role" >> "$CLAUDE_ENV_FILE"
echo "$_team_role" > "${RUNTIME_DIR}/status/${PANE_SAFE}.team_role"
```

### Role Reading in on-pre-tool-use.sh (lines 455-501)

The hook reads both tiers:

```bash
# on-pre-tool-use.sh:455-466 — Base role from env or .role file
_DOEY_ROLE="${DOEY_ROLE:-}"
if [ -n "${TMUX_PANE:-}" ]; then
  # ... resolves _RD (runtime dir), _WP (window.pane), _PS (pane_safe)
  [ -f "${_RD}/status/${_PS}.role" ] && _DOEY_ROLE=$(cat "${_RD}/status/${_PS}.role")
fi

# on-pre-tool-use.sh:468-494 — Fallback: derive role from position
if [ -z "$_DOEY_ROLE" ]; then
  # ... same window/pane logic as on-session-start.sh
fi

# on-pre-tool-use.sh:498-501 — Team role
_DOEY_TEAM_ROLE="${DOEY_TEAM_ROLE:-}"
if [ -z "$_DOEY_TEAM_ROLE" ] && [ -n "${_RD:-}" ] && [ -n "${_PS:-}" ]; then
  [ -f "${_RD}/status/${_PS}.team_role" ] && _DOEY_TEAM_ROLE=$(cat "${_RD}/status/${_PS}.team_role")
fi
```

