## 3. Boss & Taskmaster Blocking in on-pre-tool-use.sh

### The Unified Boss/Taskmaster/Subtaskmaster Block (line 598-641)

All three roles share a single blocking section:

```bash
# on-pre-tool-use.sh:598
if { [ "$_DOEY_ROLE" = "$DOEY_ROLE_ID_BOSS" ] || \
     [ "$_DOEY_ROLE" = "$DOEY_ROLE_ID_TEAM_LEAD" ] || \
     [ "$_DOEY_ROLE" = "$DOEY_ROLE_ID_COORDINATOR" ]; } && \
   [ "$TOOL_NAME" != "Bash" ]; then
  case "$TOOL_NAME" in
    Agent)
      # EXCEPTION: interviewer team_role may spawn agents
      if [ "${_DOEY_TEAM_ROLE:-}" = "interviewer" ]; then
        exit 0   # <--- team_role exception pattern
      fi
      # Block + forward
      exit 2 ;;
    Read|Edit|Write|Glob|Grep)
      _CHK_PATH=$(_json_str tool_input.file_path)
      # Boss can Read image files at any path
      if [ "$_DOEY_ROLE" = "$DOEY_ROLE_ID_BOSS" ] && [ "$TOOL_NAME" = "Read" ]; then
        case "${_CHK_PATH:-}" in
          *.png|*.jpg|...) exit 0 ;;  # <--- Boss image exception
        esac
      fi
      # PATH EXCEPTIONS: .doey/tasks/ and runtime dirs are always allowed
      case "${_CHK_PATH:-}" in
        */.doey/tasks/*|*/.doey/tasks|\
        "${_RD:-__none__}"/*|*/tmp/doey/*)
          exit 0 ;;   # <--- KEY PATH EXCEPTION PATTERN
      esac
      # Block everything else + forward
      exit 2 ;;
  esac
fi
```

### Key Path Exception Pattern (line 626-629)

This is the critical pattern for the planner integration:

```bash
case "${_CHK_PATH:-}" in
  */.doey/tasks/*|*/.doey/tasks|\
  "${_RD:-__none__}"/*|*/tmp/doey/*)
    _dbg_write "allow_${_DOEY_ROLE}_taskfile_${TOOL_NAME}"; exit 0 ;;
esac
```

**Currently allowed paths for Boss/Taskmaster/Subtaskmaster:**
- `*/.doey/tasks/*` — task files
- `${_RD}/*` — runtime directory (resolved from DOEY_RUNTIME)
- `*/tmp/doey/*` — temp doey files

**Everything else (project source) is BLOCKED with forward-to-coordinator.**

### Scratchpad Bypass (line 577-590)

All roles can access scratchpad:

```bash
# on-pre-tool-use.sh:577-590
case "$TOOL_NAME" in
  Read|Edit|Write|Glob|Grep)
    case "${_SP_PATH:-}" in
      "${_RD}/scratchpad/"*|"${_RD}/scratchpad")
        exit 0 ;;  # ALL roles bypass
    esac ;;
esac
```

